COLIGNY, North West - The family of the boy whose death sparked protests in Coligny in the North West has spoken out.Sixteen-year-old Mathlomola Moshoeu was allegedly assaulted by two white farmers after he was accused of stealing a sunflower from a farm.The suspects claim Moshoeu jumped out of a moving van as they were transporting him to hospital.The two appeared in the Coligny Magistrates Court on Friday and are facing a murder charge.eNCA spoke to Mathlomola's father, Sakkie, soon after he'd returned home from identifying his son's body on Sunday.He said it was only after learning of his son's death on Sunday that it dawned on him the protests in their town were sparked by this incident.eNCA